---
description: Next.js App Router, data loading, and project architecture
globs: "**/*.{js,jsx,ts,tsx,mjs}"
alwaysApply: false
---

- App Router: follow current project conventions; if something is unclear or deprecated, check the guide under `node_modules/next/dist/docs/`.
- Default to **Server Components**; use `"use client"` only for interactivity (state, events, browser-only APIs).
- Data: prefer server-side fetching; avoid redundant client fetching and polling.
- Rendering: prefer **static** output when content is stable; use **ISR** only when content changes on a known schedule.
- Navigation: use `next/link` for internal links.
- Fonts: use `next/font` where applicable.
- SEO: use the Metadata API for title, description, and Open Graph when needed.
- Imports: use the `@/` absolute import alias when it is already configured in the project.
- Structure: separate UI, data (fetch/loaders), utilities, and types without pointless abstractions.
- Bundles: use dynamic imports only when they clearly reduce initial JS; avoid large client trees without a good reason.
